Any class of retail on- or off-sale alcoholic beverages license issued by the Board of License Commissioners authorizes the holder to sell alcoholic beverages:
On Monday through Friday from 6 a.m. to 2 a.m. the following day;
On Saturday from 6 a.m. to 1 a.m. the following day; and
On Sunday:
For a Class A license, from 9 a.m. to 2 a.m. the following day;
For a Class B license, from 9 a.m. to 12 midnight (off-sale for beer and wine only);
For a Class C license, from 9 a.m. to 12 midnight; or
For a Class D license, from 9 a.m. to 2 a.m. (off-sale for beer and wine only).
